0018|- [HelpText]
0019|*More complicated functions, whose equations are long or consist of
0020|*conditional statements can be plotted by giving a definition with
0021|*one or several if-then-else statements as follows:
0023|*Example: Plotting the density function of the sum of 3 independent
0024|*         variables uniformly distributed over (0,1).
0025|*                                                                                                  .
0026|*XSCALE=0(1)3 YSCALE=0(0.1)1
0028|*PLOT y(x)=if(x<1)then(x*x/2)else(y2)
S   |               <
0029|*     y2=if(x<2)then(x*x/2-3*(x-1)*(x-1)/2)else((x-3)*(x-3)/2)
S   |             <
0031|*The statements may include parameters whose values are given
0032|*in the edit field. Also varying parameters are permitted.
