0040|- [HelpText]
0041|#PLOT INTEGRAL Y(X)=f(X)  (X can be any 'word')
0042|*plots the integral function of f(X). The range of integration and
0043|*plotting is given in the form X=<lower limit>,<upper limit>,<step>.
S   |                                 <           > <           > <    >
0044|*If the limits and the step (which is used both in integration and
0045|*plotting) is not given, XSCALE determines them and 1/100 of the
0046|*range is used as <step>.
S   |                  <    >
0048|*See also extra specification INTEGRAL which can be used for normalizing
0049|*of the integral on the whole range.
0051|*For example,
0052|*PLOT INTEGRAL Y(X)=EXP(-0.5*(X/sigma)^2)
0053|*     INTEGRAL=1 XSCALE=-8(2)8 YSCALE=0(0.1)1 sigma=1,2,0.5
0055|*plots the cumulative distribution function of N(0,sigma^2) for
0056|*sigma=1,1.5,2. Observe that INTEGRAL=1 normalizes the integral
0057|*to 1 on the interval (-8,8) in this case and so the constant multiplier
0058|*1/(sqr(2*pi)*sigma) can be dropped from the normal density.
0059|- shadow a: [LINK(q16_01.html)]
