0079|- [HelpText]
0080|#INTEGRAL=<positive constant>
S   |          <                 >
0081|*(in PLOT operation for curves)
0082|*normalizes the the function to be plotted so that the integral of
0083|*the function on the range of plotting is equal to the constant given
0084|*by INTEGRAL. The standard trapezoid rule is used in numeric integration
0085|*and the step length is same as in plotting.
