0093|#FILL=<density value>,<initial value>,<final value>
S   |      <             > <             > <           >
0094|*(in PLOT operation for curves) draws line segments parallel to Y axis
0095|*from the points on the curve to X axis in the interval defined by the
0096|*optional parameters <initial value>,<final value>. Default is the whole
S   |                     <             > <           >
0097|*plotting range.
0098|*<density value> (an integer 1,2,3...) gives the gap between the
S   | <             >
0099|*consecutive fill lines as a multiple of the plotting step.
0100|#YFILL=<density value>,<initial value>,<final value>
S   |       <             > <             > <           >
0101|*works as FILL but draws horizontal fill lines.
0102|#OFILL=<density value>,<initial value>,<final value>
S   |       <             > <             > <           >
0103|*draws fill lines from the points on the curve to origin (0,0).
0104|#IFILL=<density value>,<initial value>,<final value>
S   |       <             > <             > <           >
0105|*draws fill lines from the points on the curve to the initial point
0106|*of the current curve.
